	<summary>
	1/5/1993--Introduced.
Bars the recovery of damages, interest, costs, or attorney fees under the Clayton Act or similar State laws from any medical self-regulatory entity as a result of standard setting or enforcement activities designed to promote the quality of health care.

	</summary>
